HEADWORD: Teratology
<hw>Ter`a*tol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
a wonder, monster + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. Gr. <?/ a telling of wonders,
and F. <ets>t⟦eacute⟧ratologie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
branch of biological science which treats of monstrosities,
malformations, or deviations from the normal type of structure, either
in plants or animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affectation of sublimity; bombast.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teratoma</ent>⟦br⟧
